26#include <sys/cdefs.h>
27__KERNEL_RCSID(0, "$NetBSD: nouveau_nvkm_core_engine.c,v 1.3 2018/08/27 07:39:20 riastradh Exp $");
28
29#include <core/engine.h>
30#include <core/device.h>
31#include <core/option.h>
32
33#include <subdev/fb.h>
34
35void
36nvkm_engine_unref(struct nvkm_engine **pengine)
37{
38 struct nvkm_engine *engine = *pengine;
39 if (engine) {
40 mutex_lock(&engine->subdev.mutex);
41 if (--engine->usecount == 0)
42 nvkm_subdev_fini(&engine->subdev, false);
43 mutex_unlock(&engine->subdev.mutex);
44 *pengine = NULL;
45 }
46}
47
48struct nvkm_engine *
49nvkm_engine_ref(struct nvkm_engine *engine)
50{
51 if (engine) {
52 mutex_lock(&engine->subdev.mutex);
53 if (++engine->usecount == 1) {
54 int ret = nvkm_subdev_init(&engine->subdev);
55 if (ret) {
56 engine->usecount--;
57 mutex_unlock(&engine->subdev.mutex);
58 return ERR_PTR(ret);
59 }
60 }
61 mutex_unlock(&engine->subdev.mutex);
62 }
63 return engine;
64}
65
66void
67nvkm_engine_tile(struct nvkm_engine *engine, int region)
68{
69 struct nvkm_fb *fb = engine->subdev.device->fb;
70 if (engine->func->tile)
71 engine->func->tile(engine, region, &fb->tile.region[region]);
72}
73
74static void
75nvkm_engine_intr(struct nvkm_subdev *subdev)
76{
77 struct nvkm_engine *engine = nvkm_engine(subdev);
78 if (engine->func->intr)
79 engine->func->intr(engine);
80}
81
82static int
83nvkm_engine_fini(struct nvkm_subdev *subdev, bool suspend)
84{
85 struct nvkm_engine *engine = nvkm_engine(subdev);
86 if (engine->func->fini)
87 return engine->func->fini(engine, suspend);
88 return 0;
89}
90
91static int
92nvkm_engine_init(struct nvkm_subdev *subdev)
93{
94 struct nvkm_engine *engine = nvkm_engine(subdev);
95 struct nvkm_fb *fb = subdev->device->fb;
96 int ret = 0, i;
97 s64 time;
98
99 if (!engine->usecount) {
100 nvkm_trace(subdev, "init skipped, engine has no users\n");
101 return ret;
102 }
103
104 if (engine->func->oneinit && !engine->subdev.oneinit) {
105 nvkm_trace(subdev, "one-time init running...\n");
106 time = ktime_to_us(ktime_get());
107 ret = engine->func->oneinit(engine);
108 if (ret) {
109 nvkm_trace(subdev, "one-time init failed, %d\n", ret);
110 return ret;
111 }
112
113 engine->subdev.oneinit = true;
114 time = ktime_to_us(ktime_get()) - time;
115 nvkm_trace(subdev, "one-time init completed in %"PRId64"us\n", time);
116 }
117
118 if (engine->func->init)
119 ret = engine->func->init(engine);
120
121 for (i = 0; fb && i < fb->tile.regions; i++)
122 nvkm_engine_tile(engine, i);
123 return ret;
124}
125
126static void *
127nvkm_engine_dtor(struct nvkm_subdev *subdev)
128{
129 struct nvkm_engine *engine = nvkm_engine(subdev);
130 if (engine->func->dtor)
131 return engine->func->dtor(engine);
132 return engine;
133}
134
135static const struct nvkm_subdev_func
136nvkm_engine_func = {
137 .dtor = nvkm_engine_dtor,
138 .init = nvkm_engine_init,
139 .fini = nvkm_engine_fini,
140 .intr = nvkm_engine_intr,
141};
142
143int
144nvkm_engine_ctor(const struct nvkm_engine_func *func,
145 struct nvkm_device *device, int index, u32 pmc_enable,
146 bool enable, struct nvkm_engine *engine)
147{
148 nvkm_subdev_ctor(&nvkm_engine_func, device, index,
149 pmc_enable, &engine->subdev);
150 engine->func = func;
151
152 if (!nvkm_boolopt(device->cfgopt, nvkm_subdev_name[index], enable)) {
153 nvkm_debug(&engine->subdev, "disabled\n");
154 return -ENODEV;
155 }
156
157 spin_lock_init(&engine->lock);
158 return 0;
159}
160
161int
162nvkm_engine_new_(const struct nvkm_engine_func *func,
163 struct nvkm_device *device, int index, u32 pmc_enable,
164 bool enable, struct nvkm_engine **pengine)
165{
166 if (!(*pengine = kzalloc(sizeof(**pengine), GFP_KERNEL)))
167 return -ENOMEM;
168 return nvkm_engine_ctor(func, device, index, pmc_enable,
169 enable, *pengine);
170}
